\v 23 \w But|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w time|strong="G5610"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w*, \w in|strong="G1722"\w* fact \w now|strong="G3568"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w*, \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* genuine \w worshipers|strong="G4353"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* truth. Really, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w looking|strong="G2212"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \bd \w such|strong="G5108"\w*\bd* \w people|strong="G1510"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 4:23 \ft The Father “is looking” for those who will worship Him in spirit and truth. It may be that we have here a window on the reason why God created a race such as ours—persons in His image with the capacity to \bd \nd choose\nd*\bd*. God “is looking” for something, which means He does not have it, at least not automatically, nor in sufficient quantity. I take it that He wants to be appreciated for who He is, but to have meaning such appreciation cannot come from robots—it has to be voluntary. So He created a type of being with that capacity, but He had to take the risk that such a being would choose \nd not\nd* to appreciate Him. Unfortunately, most human beings make the negative choice, and with that negative choice come all sorts of negative consequences. Ever since Adam humans are born with an inclination toward sin, so for someone to choose to appreciate God is definitely not automatic, nor even easy. No one can reasonably accuse God of having ‘stacked the deck’ in His own favor, of ‘buying votes’—He seems to have done just the opposite. If a human being, against his natural inclination, chooses to appreciate God, then He receives what He is looking for. “In spirit and truth” presumably means that it cannot be faked, cannot be forced, cannot be merely physical, cannot be merely emotional (though both body and emotions can, and often will, be utilized).\f*
\v 24 \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \nd \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*\nd*,\f + \fr 4:24 \ft Again the lack of the definite article presents us with an ambiguity; the rendering ‘a spirit’ is possible. But as I indicate by the underlining, I understand that the quality inherent in the noun is being emphasized.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w must|strong="G1163"\w* \w worship|strong="G4352"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* truth.”
\p 
