\c 7
\ms1 Passover, 29 AD
\m 
\v 1 \w After|strong="G3326"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* continued \w to|strong="G2532"\w* move \w about|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Galilee|strong="G1056"\w*,\f + \fr 7:1 \ft All of chapter six took place in Galilee, so why make a point of Jesus' continuing there? 6:4 says that the Passover was near, but 7:2 says that the Feast of Tabernacles was near—that is six months later. As a God-fearing male, Jesus had to go to Jerusalem for the Passover, so He must have gone, although none of the Gospels records it. I take it that He went without calling attention to Himself, and returned immediately to Galilee, for the reason given in the second half of the verse.\f* \w since|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w wish|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* move \w about|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Judea|strong="G2453"\w* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w wanting|strong="G2309"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* kill \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 7:1 \ft Between 6:71 and 7:2 six months elapsed. For events that occurred during that period see Matthew 15:1-18:35, Mark 7:1-9:50 and Luke 9:18-50.\f*
\s1 Jesus and His brothers
\p 
\v 2 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*' \w Feast|strong="G1859"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w Tabernacles|strong="G4634"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w near|strong="G1451"\w*.
