\v 5 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w not|strong="G3761"\w* \w even|strong="G3761"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* brothers \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w believing|strong="G4100"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 7:5 \ft Well now, those brothers were not very nice, were they? I take it that they knew very well that the hierarchy was plotting to kill Jesus (it seems to me obvious that the Jews had researched Jesus' past and family, and had doubtless been working on His brothers), so they were trying to send Him to His death. With friends like that, who needs enemies?\f*
\p 
\v 6 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\nd \w My|strong="G1699"\w*\nd* \w time|strong="G2540"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G1510"\w* \w here|strong="G3918"\w* \w yet|strong="G1161"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \nd \w your|strong="G5212"\w*\nd* \w time|strong="G2540"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* available.\f + \fr 7:6 \ft I assume that He meant that they could repent and believe into Him at any time.\f*
\v 7 \w The|strong="G1161"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w cannot|strong="G1410"\w* \w hate|strong="G3404"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w does|strong="G1510"\w* \w hate|strong="G3404"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w testify|strong="G3140"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w its|strong="G3754"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w malignant|strong="G4190"\w*.\f + \fr 7:7 \ft If we raise the standard of biblical values in the public arena, calling a spade a spade, the world will hate us too—try it and see!\f*
\v 8 \w You|strong="G5210"\w* guys \w go|strong="G1519"\w* \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w feast|strong="G1859"\w*; \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w going|strong="G3778"\w* \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w yet|strong="G3768"\w*\f + \fr 7:8 \ft Perhaps 3% of the Greek manuscripts, of inferior quality, omit “yet” (as in NASB, TEV, RSV, etc.). The reading of the so-called ‘critical’ text has the effect of ascribing a falsehood to Jesus, since He did in fact go to the feast (and doubtless knew what He was going to do). Among the 97% are 𝕻\sup 66,75\sup* and B—since the UBS editors usually attach the highest value to 𝕻\sup 75\sup* and B, isn't it strange that they reject them in this case?\f* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w feast|strong="G1859"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w time|strong="G2540"\w* \w has|strong="G3778"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w yet|strong="G3768"\w* \w fully|strong="G4137"\w* \w come|strong="G3756"\w*.”
\v 9 \w So|strong="G1161"\w* \w upon|strong="G1722"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w He|strong="G1161"\w* \w stayed|strong="G3306"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Galilee|strong="G1056"\w*.\f + \fr 7:9 \ft That is, His brothers started out on their way to Jerusalem and Jesus stayed behind, for the moment.\f*
\ms1 Jesus leaves Galilee—the last six months of His public ministry
\p 
\v 10 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w when|strong="G1161"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* brothers \w had|strong="G2532"\w* gone \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w feast|strong="G1859"\w*, \w then|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* \w up|strong="G1519"\w*, \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w openly|strong="G5320"\w* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w secret|strong="G2927"\w* \w like|strong="G5613"\w*.
