\v 16 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w What|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* teach \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w mine|strong="G1699"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w sent|strong="G3992"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.\f + \fr 7:16 \ft Jesus is evidently aware of what they are saying or thinking, since He addresses it.\f*
