\s1 The last day of the Feast
\p 
\v 37 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w on|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w last|strong="G2078"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* most \w important|strong="G3173"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Feast|strong="G1859"\w*, \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w up|strong="G2476"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G3004"\w* \w out|strong="G2896"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w If|strong="G1437"\w* \w anyone|strong="G5100"\w* \w thirsts|strong="G1372"\w*, \w let|strong="G1161"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w drink|strong="G4095"\w*.
\v 38 \w The|strong="G1519"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w believing|strong="G4100"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w has|strong="G1473"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w innermost|strong="G2836"\w* \w being|strong="G2836"\w* \w will|strong="G1473"\w* \w flow|strong="G4482"\w* \w rivers|strong="G4215"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w living|strong="G2198"\w* \w water|strong="G5204"\w*.”\f + \fr 7:38 \ft Just where does the Scripture say this, and why “rivers” (pl); wouldn't one be enough? Reference Bibles will give a variety of suggestions, none of which really fit. I personally believe that the reference is to Ezekiel 47:1-12, and most especially to verse 9 where the Hebrew text has two rivers (or torrents)—when that river got to the Dead Sea it evidently divided, so as to go along both banks at once. Living water takes life and health wherever it goes. So how much living water is flowing out of me, or you? The secret of that water is given in verse 12: “their water flows from the sanctuary” (compare 1 Corinthians 6:19).\f*
\v 39 (\w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w He|strong="G1161"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*, \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w believing|strong="G4100"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w going|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w receive|strong="G2983"\w*,\f + \fr 7:39 \ft When you believe into Jesus you receive the Holy Spirit.\f* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w not|strong="G1510"\w* \w yet|strong="G1161"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* \it given\it* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w not|strong="G1510"\w* \w yet|strong="G1161"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* \w glorified|strong="G1392"\w*.)
\p 
