\p 
\v 14 “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w good|strong="G2570"\w* \w shepherd|strong="G4166"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w own|strong="G1699"\w* \it sheep\it*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w known|strong="G1097"\w* \w by|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 15 \w Just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w knows|strong="G1097"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w lay|strong="G5087"\w* \w down|strong="G5087"\w* \w my|strong="G5087"\w* \w life|strong="G5590"\w* \w on|strong="G5228"\w* \w behalf|strong="G5228"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sheep|strong="G4263"\w*.
\v 16 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w other|strong="G1520"\w* \w sheep|strong="G4263"\w*, \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w fold|strong="G4167"\w*;\f + \fr 10:16 \ft “This fold” presumably refers to Israel, so the “other sheep” would be Gentiles. Paul develops this theme in Ephesians 2:11-22.\f* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w must|strong="G1163"\w* \w bring|strong="G2532"\w* \nd \w them|strong="G3588"\w*\nd* \w also|strong="G2532"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* listen \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w flock|strong="G4167"\w*, \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w shepherd|strong="G4166"\w*.
\p 
\v 17 “\w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* loves \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w in|strong="G1223"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w lay|strong="G5087"\w* \w down|strong="G5087"\w* \w my|strong="G5087"\w* \w life|strong="G5590"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w up|strong="G5087"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*.
\v 18 \w No|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w takes|strong="G2983"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w lay|strong="G5087"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w down|strong="G5087"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w myself|strong="G1683"\w*.\f + \fr 10:18 \ft This is important! The cross did not kill Jesus; He dismissed His spirit—see John 19:30 and Matthew 27:50. In Mark 15:39 the loud shout followed immediately by death convinced the centurion. He had seen many crucifixions and was doubtless hardened to it. He knew that a person on a cross dies from asphyxiation. The weight of the body pushes the diaphragm against the lungs and you cannot breathe. Nailing the feet was a sadistic procedure that prolonged the agony—rather than die they would push against the nail to get a breath. Finally, when too weak to do that they would die for lack of air. (That is why they broke the legs of the two thieves; they then died within a few minutes.) Obviously, if you are dying without air you cannot shout! The centurion knew that the cross had not killed Jesus. But what mere human can just tell his spirit to leave? 2 + 2 = 4. Jesus had to be the Son of God.\f* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w lay|strong="G5087"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w down|strong="G5087"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w up|strong="G2532"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*. \w This|strong="G3778"\w* \w command|strong="G1785"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w my|strong="G5087"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*.”\f + \fr 10:18 \ft The whole procedure was part of the Plan. An ordinary human being can kill himself, all right, but cannot change his mind later and come back. To Jesus the Father gave the ability to reunite spirit and body—presumably a unique occurrence.\f*
\p 
\v 19 \w Therefore|strong="G1223"\w* \w there|strong="G1096"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w another|strong="G3825"\w* \w division|strong="G4978"\w* \w among|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w because|strong="G1223"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w words|strong="G3056"\w*.
\v 20 \w Many|strong="G4183"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w them|strong="G3004"\w* \w were|strong="G2532"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w demon|strong="G1140"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G5101"\w* raving \w mad|strong="G3105"\w*. \w Why|strong="G5101"\w* \w do|strong="G5101"\w* \w you|strong="G3004"\w* listen \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G2532"\w*?”
\v 21 \w Others|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w These|strong="G3778"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w sayings|strong="G4487"\w* \w of|strong="G4487"\w* someone \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* demonized. \w A|strong="G1510"\w* \w demon|strong="G1140"\w* \w cannot|strong="G1410"\w* open \w blind|strong="G5185"\w* \w people|strong="G1510"\w*'s \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w*, \w can|strong="G1410"\w* \w it|strong="G3778"\w*?”\f + \fr 10:21 \ft So they thought, but on the basis of what happens in Spiritist and Satanist circles, it appears that if a demon causes blindness (which they can), the same or a stronger one can remove it.\f*
\s2 “My sheep hear my voice”
\p 
\v 22 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G1161"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Feast|strong="G1456"\w* \w of|strong="G1722"\w* \w Dedication|strong="G1456"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="G2414"\w*;\f + \fr 10:22 \ft Chapter 8 happened on Oct. 18, 29 (I think). Chapter 9 and 10:1-21 presumably happened shortly after. Here in 10:22 it is Dec. 17, 29—two months later. I suppose that Luke 10:1-14:24 occurred during those two months; which means that the seventy were sent out during the last six months of the Lord's earthly ministry. Their target was interior Judea, in contrast to the twelve, whose target was Galilee.\f* \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G1161"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w winter|strong="G5494"\w*.
\v 23 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w walking|strong="G4043"\w* \w about|strong="G1722"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w temple|strong="G2413"\w*,\f + \fr 10:23 \ft It was probably cold and He was walking to stay warm.\f* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Solomon|strong="G4672"\w*'s \w porch|strong="G4745"\w*.
\v 24 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w surrounded|strong="G2944"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w How|strong="G2193"\w* \w long|strong="G2193"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* keep \w us|strong="G3004"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w suspense|strong="G5590"\w*? \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w tell|strong="G3004"\w* \w us|strong="G3004"\w* \w plainly|strong="G3954"\w*.”
\v 25 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w did|strong="G4160"\w* \w tell|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w*.\f + \fr 10:25 \ft Quite right. Their ‘suspense’ was pretended; they simply did not want to acknowledge Him. So they twist and squirm.\f* \w The|strong="G1722"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*'s \w name|strong="G3686"\w*—\w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w testify|strong="G3140"\w* \w concerning|strong="G4012"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.
\v 26 \w But|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w do|strong="G4100"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w among|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w sheep|strong="G4263"\w*, \w just|strong="G3588"\w* like \w I|strong="G3754"\w* told \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.\f + \fr 10:26 \ft When was that? Probably two months before, as recorded earlier in this chapter.\f*
\v 27 \nd \w My|strong="G1699"\w*\nd* \w sheep|strong="G4263"\w* \w hear|strong="G5456"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* follow \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.
\v 28 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* eternal \w life|strong="G2222"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w never|strong="G3756"\w* \w ever|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G2532"\w* wasted; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w one|strong="G5100"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* snatch \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1325"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w*.\f + \fr 10:28 \ft Being snatched is one thing; jumping out is another. You can't ‘snatch’ yourself, it must be done by an outside force, and no such force is greater than God. But, if you don't want to go to Heaven, you won't. Jesus puts it very plainly in John 15:6, “If anyone does not abide in me, he is cast out as a branch…” ‘Abiding’ is up to us; we are not forced to do it. If we choose not to, we are out.\f*
\v 29 \w My|strong="G3956"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w has|strong="G3962"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \it them\it* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w greater|strong="G3173"\w* \w than|strong="G3173"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w*;\f + \fr 10:29 \ft About 0.5% of the Greek manuscripts (with variations), of objectively inferior quality, read “What my Father has given me is greater than all” (as in TEV, etc.).\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w able|strong="G1410"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* snatch \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G3956"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*'s \w hand|strong="G5495"\w*.
\v 30 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w*.”
\p 
\v 31 \w Therefore|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* picked up \w stones|strong="G3037"\w*\f + \fr 10:31 \ft The temple courts were paved and presumably swept with some regularity. So how come there were stones lying around? I imagine there were piles of stones, of the right size and strategically placed, precisely for moments like this one. (If stoning serious offenders is an obligation, you need to be prepared.)\f* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w stone|strong="G3037"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 32 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* answered \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Many|strong="G4183"\w* \w good|strong="G2570"\w* \w works|strong="G2041"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w shown|strong="G1166"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*. \w For|strong="G1223"\w* \w which|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w stoning|strong="G3034"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*?”
\v 33 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* answered \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w saying|strong="G3754"\w*, “\w It|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w good|strong="G2570"\w* \w work|strong="G2041"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w we|strong="G3754"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w stoning|strong="G3034"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* blasphemy; precisely \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \nd \w you|strong="G4771"\w*\nd*, \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w man|strong="G3756"\w*, \w make|strong="G4160"\w* \w yourself|strong="G4572"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*!”
\v 34 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Is|strong="G1510"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w your|strong="G1722"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, ‘\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w gods|strong="G2316"\w*’?\f + \fr 10:34 \ft The reference is to Psalm 82:6, where the speaker is God (verse 1). Jesus calls the Psalms ‘law’.\f*
\v 35 \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w called|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* ‘\w gods|strong="G2316"\w*’ \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w came|strong="G1096"\w*—\w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w cannot|strong="G1410"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w broken|strong="G3089"\w*\f + \fr 10:35 \ft The Lord inserts this as an aside, but it is an important statement in itself—Scripture cannot be broken. If we build our lives on God's Word we have a secure foundation, one that cannot be shaken. (Your faith in that Word may be shaken, but not the Word itself.)\f*—
\v 36 \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* ‘\w You|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* blaspheming’ \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G3739"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* sanctified \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w sent|strong="G2316"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, ‘\w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*'s \w Son|strong="G5207"\w*’?
