\p 
\v 31 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* answered \w them|strong="G4100"\w*: “\w Do|strong="G4100"\w* \w you|strong="G2424"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w* now, \it really\it*?
\v 32 \w Listen|strong="G2400"\w*, \w an|strong="G2532"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w*, \w actually|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w has|strong="G3962"\w* already \w arrived|strong="G2064"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w scattered|strong="G4650"\w*, \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w his|strong="G1519"\w* \w own|strong="G2398"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* leave \nd \w me|strong="G1473"\w*\nd* \w alone|strong="G3441"\w*.\f + \fr 16:32 \ft It happened that very night.\f* \w Yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w alone|strong="G3441"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.
\v 33 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w spoken|strong="G2980"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w peace|strong="G1515"\w*. \w In|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* oppression;\f + \fr 16:33 \ft Just so. Any system dominated by Satan will be oppressive, for everybody, but his special malice will be directed at those who serve Christ.\f* \w but|strong="G3588"\w* \w take|strong="G2293"\w* heart, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w conquered|strong="G3528"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*!”\f + \fr 16:33 \ft Yes, amen! I take it that the ‘world’ here refers to the world system controlled by Satan. Jesus did indeed conquer it. He lived within that system for 33 years without ever succumbing to it, without ever being tainted by it. Since He conquered the world, we can too! So let's take heart!\f*
\c 17
\s1 Jesus prays
\m 
\v 1 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w spoke|strong="G2980"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w*,\f + \fr 17:1 \ft I take it that ‘these things’ is cataphoric, referring forward to the content of the prayer.\f* raising \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w eyes|strong="G3788"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Heaven|strong="G3772"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*:
\s2 \w For|strong="G1519"\w* \w Himself|strong="G1519"\w*
\p “\w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w has|strong="G3962"\w* \w come|strong="G2064"\w*! \w Glorify|strong="G1392"\w* \w Your|strong="G2532"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w Your|strong="G2532"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w glorify|strong="G1392"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*,
\v 2 \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w You|strong="G3739"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w Him|strong="G1325"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w over|strong="G1849"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w humanity|strong="G4561"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w He|strong="G3739"\w* \w will|strong="G3739"\w* \w give|strong="G1325"\w* eternal \w life|strong="G2222"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w those|strong="G3739"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G3956"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w Him|strong="G1325"\w*.\f + \fr 17:2 \ft Here is a clear statement of divine participation in our salvation. The whole process is under the authority of the Father.\f*
\v 3 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* eternal \w life|strong="G2222"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w*: \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*,\f + \fr 17:3 \ft I take it that the reference here is to experiential knowledge. ‘Eternal life’ refers mainly to a quality of life (more than longevity), and that quality is defined by relationship with the Father. The person who conceives of God as a distant, detached authority figure doesn't really know Him.\f* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w only|strong="G3441"\w* \w true|strong="G3588"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w One|strong="G3739"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w sent|strong="G2316"\w*—\w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*.\f + \fr 17:3 \ft This is the first recorded time that the Lord used this title, ‘Jesus Christ’ (in Matthew 16:20 there is ‘Jesus, the Christ’—as in over 95% of the Greek manuscripts). He did so when He could also say, “I have finished the work that You have given me to do” (next verse) (He still had a few hours to go, but is declaring His victory). In Acts and the epistles the title is very frequent—it affirms that Jesus is the Messiah. Also, what happens to those who only ‘know’ the Father, but not the Son?\f*
\v 4 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w glorified|strong="G1392"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1909"\w* \w earth|strong="G1093"\w*. \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w finished|strong="G5048"\w* \w the|strong="G1909"\w* \w work|strong="G2041"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w do|strong="G4160"\w*.\f + \fr 17:4 \ft The older I get, finishing ‘the work You have given me to do’ looms larger and larger in my mind.\f*
\v 5 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w*, \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w glorify|strong="G1392"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w by|strong="G3844"\w* \w Your|strong="G2192"\w* \w side|strong="G3844"\w* \w with|strong="G3844"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w along|strong="G2532"\w* \w with|strong="G3844"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w before|strong="G4253"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w existed|strong="G1510"\w*!\f + \fr 17:5 \ft As it says in 1 Peter 1:19-20, the Lamb, with His blood shed, was foreknown before the foundation of the world. Colossians 1:16, Hebrews 1:10 and John 1:3,10 make clear that the Son was the primary agent in the creation of this planet. So Jehovah the Son is both Creator and Lamb—before He created He knew that man would rebel and He Himself would have to pay the terrible ransom. From our Lord's statement here I get the impression that as soon as the Son started dealing with this planet He gave up some of His glory. So now He is asking to have it back. Ephesians 1:20-21 makes clear that the Father granted His request, the Son is back where He was before. And He took us with Him (Ephesians 2:6)! Thank You, Lord!! Also, our Lord's statement here goes against any ‘Gnostic’ type view that has Jesus beginning as an inferior being and working up through successive levels of perfection, or what have you.\f*
\s2 For the Apostles
\p 
\v 6 “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w revealed|strong="G5319"\w* \w Your|strong="G4674"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*\f + \fr 17:6 \ft “Your name” = “You”; a person's name represents that person. This is very clear in John 3:18. Jesus revealed the Father to the world.\f* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w men|strong="G3588"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*. \w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \nd \w Yours|strong="G4771"\w*\nd* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w kept|strong="G5083"\w* \w Your|strong="G4674"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w*.
\v 7 \w They|strong="G3754"\w* \w now|strong="G3568"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w everything|strong="G3956"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \nd \w You|strong="G4771"\w*\nd*;
\v 8 \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sayings|strong="G4487"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w known|strong="G1097"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w sure|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w came|strong="G1831"\w* \w forth|strong="G1831"\w* \w from|strong="G3844"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*,\f + \fr 17:8 \ft Over and over again the Lord returns to the theme of their knowing and believing where He came from, His divine origin. So this must be important! Someone who does not believe that Jesus is God cannot be a true Christian.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w believed|strong="G4100"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w sent|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*.
\v 9 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w praying|strong="G2065"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*; \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w praying|strong="G2065"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w but|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w yours|strong="G4771"\w*.
\v 10 \w Actually|strong="G2532"\w*, \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w Yours|strong="G4674"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Yours|strong="G4674"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w mine|strong="G1699"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* \w glorified|strong="G1392"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 11 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3765"\w* \w longer|strong="G3765"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*,\f + \fr 17:11 \ft He would still be around for another forty days, or so, but the countdown has begun.\f* \w yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w these|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*.
\p “Holy \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w keep|strong="G5083"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Your|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w*.\f + \fr 17:11 \ft I imagine that this will only be fully realized after we are glorified.\f*
\v 12 \w While|strong="G1722"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* world \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w kept|strong="G5083"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Your|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w*. \w I|strong="G1473"\w* protected \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* lost \w except|strong="G1487"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* perdition, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w fulfilled|strong="G4137"\w*.\f + \fr 17:12 \ft This is perhaps the clearest of a very few passages in the Bible that might be said to indicate what has been called ‘double predestination’ or ‘preterition’, that is, that someone is predestined to be lost. In Hebrew usage (Jesus, a Jew among Jews, was presumably speaking Hebrew here) a ‘son’ of something is characterized by that something; so a ‘son of perdition’ is characterized by lostness; the Scripture in question would be part of the Old Testament and hence written long before the person was born. (I have not been able to locate a clear text to that effect, but there are indirect ones.)\f*
\v 13 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w speak|strong="G2980"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \nd \w my|strong="G1699"\w*\nd* \w joy|strong="G5479"\w* \w made|strong="G4137"\w* \w full|strong="G4137"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.\f + \fr 17:13 \ft Although He was addressing the Father, Jesus evidently did so out loud—precisely so that the disciples would hear, with a view to joy.\f*
\p 
\v 14 “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w Your|strong="G2532"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w*;\f + \fr 17:14 \ft Yes! Oh praise God! That Word delivers us from Satan's kingdom in every way, including worldview. So it is only natural that Satan's ‘world’ will hate us.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w has|strong="G2889"\w* \w hated|strong="G3404"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.
\v 15 \w I|strong="G2443"\w* \w am|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w asking|strong="G2065"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w You|strong="G1438"\w* \w take|strong="G2443"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w but|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w You|strong="G1438"\w* \w keep|strong="G5083"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w malignant|strong="G4190"\w* \w one|strong="G1438"\w*.\f + \fr 17:15 \ft “The malignant one” is Satan. Satan got one of the twelve, but must not get any more of them.\f*
\v 16 \w They|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.\f + \fr 17:16 \ft He repeats what He just said in verse 14, so it must be important. Jesus was not of this world because He literally came from Heaven, which could not be said of those disciples. But in the context of verse 15 the reference is probably to the ‘world’ dominated by Satan, the system. Their allegiance is no longer to Satan's system.\f*
\v 17 Sanctify \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w by|strong="G1722"\w* \w Your|strong="G4674"\w* Truth; \nd \w Your|strong="G4674"\w*\nd* \w Word|strong="G3056"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* Truth.\f + \fr 17:17 \ft The Word is what the Holy Spirit uses to sanctify us; it is His ‘sword’ (Ephesians 6:17, Hebrews 4:12).\f*
\v 18 \w Just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w You|strong="G1438"\w* sent \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w also|strong="G2504"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* sent \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.\f + \fr 17:18 \ft See John 20:21.\f*
\v 19 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G5228"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w sakes|strong="G5228"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* sanctify \w myself|strong="G1683"\w*,\f + \fr 17:19 \ft To ‘sanctify’ something to God means to separate/dedicate/consecrate it for His exclusive use. While on earth Jesus concentrated His attention and energies on a single goal, to execute the Plan, the Father's will. To the extent that we pay attention to the Truth, we will do the same.\f* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* sanctified \w in|strong="G1722"\w* truth.
\s2 For all believers
\p 
\v 20 “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w pray|strong="G2065"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w only|strong="G3440"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w through|strong="G1223"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w*;
\v 21 \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w*, \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*, \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*; \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Us|strong="G2249"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w sent|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.
\v 22 \w In|strong="G3588"\w* fact, \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w You|strong="G3739"\w* \w gave|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*,\f + \fr 17:22 \ft What ‘glory’ was that? In Romans 3:23 I imagine that the ‘glory’ of God has to do with His essence, His character. The new ‘man’ or nature that a regenerated person receives is related to that essence/character. It is that nature in common that makes us ‘one’. However, since most Christians seldom allow the new nature to control them, in practice we don't see all that much unity. But in Heaven it will come to fruition.\f* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w We|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w*:
\v 23 \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w perfected|strong="G5048"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w*; \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w sent|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* loved \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* loved \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.\f + \fr 17:23 \ft Tremendous!\f*
\p 
\v 24 “\w Father|strong="G3962"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2309"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w desire|strong="G2309"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w also|strong="G2548"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w*,\f + \fr 17:24 \ft He wants His bride.\f* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w may|strong="G2443"\w* \w observe|strong="G2334"\w* \nd \w my|strong="G1699"\w*\nd* \w glory|strong="G1391"\w*, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G2309"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w You|strong="G3739"\w* loved \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w before|strong="G4253"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* founding \w of|strong="G1391"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*.
\v 25 \w Righteous|strong="G1342"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*! \w Indeed|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w* \w has|strong="G3962"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w known|strong="G1097"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w known|strong="G1097"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w known|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w sent|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*.
\v 26 Yes, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G1107"\w* \w Your|strong="G2532"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w known|strong="G1107"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G1510"\w* \w make|strong="G1107"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w known|strong="G1107"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* love \w with|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* loved \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.”\f + \fr 17:26 \ft Here is the ‘spiral’ again; the more we know, the more we love, the more we obey…\f*
\c 18
\s1 Betrayal and arrest
\m 
\v 1 \w Having|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w with|strong="G4862"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w across|strong="G4008"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Kidron|strong="G2748"\w* \w ravine|strong="G5493"\w*, \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w garden|strong="G2779"\w*, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w entered|strong="G1525"\w*.
\v 2 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Judas|strong="G2455"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w betraying|strong="G3860"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w knew|strong="G1492"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w often|strong="G4178"\w* \w met|strong="G4863"\w* \w there|strong="G1563"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w*.
\v 3 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Judas|strong="G2455"\w*, \w having|strong="G2532"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* detachment \it of soldiers\it* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* operatives \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w chief|strong="G2532"\w* priests \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Pharisees|strong="G5330"\w*, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* arrives \w there|strong="G1563"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w lanterns|strong="G5322"\w*, \w torches|strong="G2985"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w weapons|strong="G3696"\w*.
\s2 Jesus knocks the soldiers down with His word
\p 
\v 4 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w knowing|strong="G1492"\w* \w everything|strong="G3956"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w going|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* happen \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w went|strong="G1831"\w* forward \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Who|strong="G5101"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G3708"\w* \w looking|strong="G2212"\w* \w for|strong="G1909"\w*?”
\v 5 \w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Natsorean.” \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w*.” (\w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Judas|strong="G2455"\w*, \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w betrayer|strong="G3860"\w*, \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*.)
\v 6 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w when|strong="G5613"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w*,” \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2532"\w* \w backward|strong="G3694"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w fell|strong="G4098"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w ground|strong="G5476"\w*!\f + \fr 18:6 \ft Have you ever tried to imagine this scene? Try imagining that you are one those soldiers, and the person you have been sent to arrest knocks you down, just with his word! So are you going to want to try anything against him, really? Hey, I think I would get up and run away as fast and as far as I could! I see two miracles here: 1) He knocked them down with His word; 2) He obliged them to stay there and get on with their job, because it was the appointed time for Him to be taken, tried and crucified. But He made it perfectly clear that He was in control of the situation.\f*
\v 7 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w He|strong="G1161"\w* \w asked|strong="G1905"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*, “\w Who|strong="G5101"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G3004"\w* \w looking|strong="G2212"\w* \w for|strong="G1161"\w*?” \w And|strong="G1161"\w* \w they|strong="G1161"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* Natsorean.”
\v 8 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w told|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w he|strong="G3754"\w*. \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \nd \w me|strong="G1473"\w*\nd* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w looking|strong="G2212"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w*, allow \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w men|strong="G3778"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w go|strong="G5217"\w*”
\v 9 (\w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G3739"\w* \w spoke|strong="G3004"\w* \w might|strong="G1473"\w* \w be|strong="G3756"\w* \w fulfilled|strong="G4137"\w*, “\w Of|strong="G1537"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w did|strong="G1325"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* lose \w even|strong="G3754"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w*”).\f + \fr 18:9 \ft I take it that the Iscariot had not been given to Him by the Father, at least in the sense of 17:6—“They were \nd Yours\nd* and You gave them to me”. Presumably the Iscariot never belonged to the Father.\f*
\p 
\v 10 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w Simon|strong="G4613"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w*, \w having|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w sword|strong="G3162"\w*, \w drew|strong="G1670"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, \w struck|strong="G3817"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w high|strong="G2532"\w* priest'\w s|strong="G2192"\w* \w servant|strong="G1401"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w cut|strong="G2532"\w* off \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w right|strong="G1188"\w* \w ear|strong="G5621"\w*. (\w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w servant|strong="G1401"\w*'\w s|strong="G2192"\w* \w name|strong="G3686"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w Malchus|strong="G3124"\w*.)\f + \fr 18:10 \ft John probably knew him personally; see verse 15 below.\f*
\v 11 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w*: “Sheathe \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w sword|strong="G3162"\w*!\f + \fr 18:11 \ft We know from Luke 22:51 that Jesus healed the ear, or Peter could have been in trouble. The parallel accounts give more detail.\f* \w The|strong="G1519"\w* \w cup|strong="G4221"\w* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w has|strong="G3962"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w*, \w must|strong="G4095"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w drink|strong="G4095"\w* \w it|strong="G3739"\w*?”
\s2 To Annas first
\p 
\v 12 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* detachment, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w commander|strong="G5506"\w*\f + \fr 18:12 \ft The word here (\it chiliarch\it*) refers to a commander of a thousand men (or of a cohort = about 600); this could only be a Roman officer of high rank. So how did they get him to come along? Obviously Pilate had been informed and was participating. For a detailed discussion, please see the Appendix: “Poor Pilate—wrong place, wrong time”.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* operatives \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w arrested|strong="G4815"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w bound|strong="G1210"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 13 \w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* Annas \w first|strong="G4413"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w father-in-law|strong="G3995"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Caiaphas|strong="G2533"\w*,\f + \fr 18:13 \ft The bigger reason was that Annas was the real high priest, according to the Law (the office of high priest was for life). He was the power behind the throne, so to say. Caiaphas was the political high priest (that year), for purposes of dealing with Rome.\f* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w high|strong="G2532"\w* priest \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w year|strong="G1763"\w*.\f + \fr 18:13 \ft A careful look at the parallel accounts makes clear that all of Peter's denials took place at Caiaphas' palace, as also all the recorded questionings, etc. So between verses 13 and 15 Jesus is taken to Caiaphas (see verse 24 below).\f*
\v 14 (\w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Caiaphas|strong="G2533"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w had|strong="G1510"\w* \w advised|strong="G4823"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w it|strong="G3754"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w expedient|strong="G4851"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w man|strong="G1520"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* die \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w people|strong="G2992"\w*.)
\s1 Peter denies Jesus
\p 
\v 15 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Simon|strong="G4613"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w kept|strong="G2532"\w* following \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w as|strong="G1519"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w*. \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w known|strong="G1110"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w high|strong="G2532"\w* priest,\f + \fr 18:15 \ft Annas is never referred to as the high priest by John, so this is Caiaphas.\f* \w so|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2424"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w high|strong="G2532"\w* priest's courtyard \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.
\v 16 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \it left\it* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w outside|strong="G1854"\w* \w by|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w door|strong="G2374"\w*. \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w known|strong="G1110"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w high|strong="G2532"\w* priest, \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w spoke|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w doorkeeper|strong="G2377"\w* (f), \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w brought|strong="G1521"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w*.
\v 17 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w servant|strong="G3588"\w* girl, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w doorkeeper|strong="G2377"\w*, \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w*, “\w You|strong="G4771"\w* aren'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w man|strong="G3778"\w*'s \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w*, \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*?”\f + \fr 18:17 \ft Everyone there, including the girl, knows that John belongs to Jesus, so her question is perfectly natural, without malice—she assumes that Peter must also. Notice that Peter denies right in front of John! Don't you know that John kept his eye on Peter from that moment on!\f* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w*!”
\v 18 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w servants|strong="G1401"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* operatives \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* charcoal fire, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w cold|strong="G5592"\w*,\f + \fr 18:18 \ft It was after midnight in early April.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w warming|strong="G2328"\w* \w themselves|strong="G3326"\w*. \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w warmed|strong="G2532"\w* \w himself|strong="G2328"\w*.\f + \fr 18:18 \ft For a detailed discussion of Peter's denials, please see the Appendix: “How many times did Jesus say Peter would deny Him?”.\f*
\s2 Caiaphas interrogates Jesus
\p 
\v 19 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w high|strong="G2532"\w* priest \w questioned|strong="G2065"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w His|strong="G4012"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w His|strong="G4012"\w* \w teaching|strong="G1322"\w*.
\v 20 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* answered \w him|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w spoken|strong="G2980"\w* \w openly|strong="G3954"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*. \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* \w taught|strong="G1321"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w synagogue|strong="G4864"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w temple|strong="G2413"\w*, \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w always|strong="G3842"\w* congregate, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w spoken|strong="G2980"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3762"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w secret|strong="G2927"\w*.
\v 21 \w Why|strong="G5101"\w* \w do|strong="G5101"\w* \w you|strong="G3739"\w* \w question|strong="G2065"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*? \w Question|strong="G2065"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G1473"\w* heard \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w spoke|strong="G2980"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*. \w Sure|strong="G1492"\w*, \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w what|strong="G5101"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*.”\f + \fr 18:21 \ft The Lord's observation here was perfectly reasonable and in accord with the law. The priest should have produced witnesses, rather than asking Jesus to testify against Himself.\f*
\v 22 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w upon|strong="G3588"\w* \w His|strong="G1325"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1520"\w* \w the|strong="G1161"\w* operatives \w standing|strong="G3936"\w* \w by|strong="G3936"\w* slapped \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Is|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w how|strong="G3779"\w* \w you|strong="G1325"\w* answer \w the|strong="G1161"\w* high priest?”
\v 23 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* answered \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w spoke|strong="G2980"\w* \w wrongly|strong="G2560"\w*, identify \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w wrong|strong="G2556"\w*; \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w rightly|strong="G2573"\w*, \w why|strong="G5101"\w* \w do|strong="G5101"\w* \w you|strong="G1487"\w* hit \w me|strong="G1473"\w*?”\f + \fr 18:23 \ft Since everything that was going on was unjust and illegal, I find it to be curious that Jesus reprimanded the man.\f*
\v 24 (Annas \w had|strong="G3588"\w* sent \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w bound|strong="G1210"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w Caiaphas|strong="G2533"\w* \w the|strong="G4314"\w* high priest.)\f + \fr 18:24 \ft The eclectic text, following about 9% of the Greek manuscripts, reads “\nd then\nd* Annas sent…”, creating a conflict with the parallel passages (perhaps 1% read “but Annas sent/had sent…”). The use of parenthetical comments, or historical/cultural asides, is standard procedure for John; for a partial list see: 1:44, 2:6, 4:2,9,44, 6:4,64, 7:50, 9:14, 11:2,18-19,30-31, 12:1,\nd 6\nd*,16, 13:\nd 2\nd*,11,28-29 (there are at least a dozen more). I take it that verse 24 here is just one more instance; it is as if at this point John realizes that the reader could think that the proceedings were still going on at Annas' house.\f*
\s2 Peter again
\p 
\v 25 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w Simon|strong="G4613"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w warming|strong="G2328"\w* \w himself|strong="G2328"\w*. \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w You|strong="G4771"\w* aren'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w*, \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*?”\f + \fr 18:25 \ft We don't know what John was doing all this time, except that he was right there in that compound; I think it perfectly likely that he would talk to Peter from time to time. They knew that John was a disciple, but did not know Peter. Also, the windows of the house were doubtless open (no air conditioning), so they probably heard Caiaphas ask about His disciples. Actually, Luke 22:61 says Jesus \nd turned\nd* and looked at Peter, so the window had to be open, and Jesus was near the window but with His back to it. Since Caiaphas was presumably facing Jesus he was also facing the open window and his voice would certainly carry out to the patio. Their question was not unreasonable.\f* \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* denied \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w*!”
\v 26 \w One|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w servants|strong="G1401"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* high priest, \w a|strong="G1722"\w* \w relative|strong="G4773"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w ear|strong="G5621"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w had|strong="G1510"\w* sliced, \w says|strong="G3004"\w*, “Didn'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w garden|strong="G2779"\w*?”\f + \fr 18:26 \ft Now here we have a little malice; you can imagine the intonation in the man's voice! Peter goes into a cold sweat. I bet he was wishing he was someplace else. (I wonder if he was still wearing his sword.)\f*
\v 27 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* denied \w again|strong="G3825"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w immediately|strong="G2112"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* rooster \w crowed|strong="G5455"\w*.\f + \fr 18:27 \ft In keeping with his usual procedure, John records three denials by Peter that are not mentioned by the other Evangelists, and I would say that the rooster crow here is the first of the two (Mark 14:68, 72). A close comparison of all the details surrounding the denials (who provoked it, in what terms, when, where, Peter's response) shows that there had to be a minimum of six, more likely eight, denials—3/4 before the first rooster crow, 3/4 before the second. Peter was being satanized (Luke 22:31), and it took a look from the Lord to break the spell (Luke 22:61).\f*
\ms1 Crucifixion day
\s1 Jesus taken to Pilate
\p 
\v 28 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w led|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w Caiaphas|strong="G2533"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Praetorium|strong="G4232"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w early|strong="G4404"\w* \w morning|strong="G4404"\w*. \w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1519"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w enter|strong="G1525"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Praetorium|strong="G4232"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w would|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w defiled|strong="G3392"\w* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w could|strong="G3361"\w* \w eat|strong="G2068"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Passover|strong="G3957"\w*.\f + \fr 18:28 \ft Aren't these guys cute? They are perpetrating a totally illegal and immoral plot, but they think they are squeaky clean, no problem—but to set foot in the Praetorium, now that would be dirty! If your values are twisted, you are twisted.\f*
\v 29 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 18:29 \ft It seems to me obvious that the hierarchy had made a deal with Pilate; he was waiting. Hey, you do not go marching up to the Governor's headquarters at 5:30 a.m. and demand a hearing; and there is no indication that Pilate came out in his pajamas. He was up, dressed and waiting.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G5346"\w*, “\w What|strong="G5101"\w* \w accusation|strong="G2724"\w* \w do|strong="G5101"\w* \w you|strong="G1438"\w* \w bring|strong="G5342"\w* \w against|strong="G2596"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w man|strong="G3778"\w*?”
\v 30 \w In|strong="G2532"\w* \w reply|strong="G3004"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G4160"\w*, “\w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w an|strong="G2532"\w* evil-doer \w we|strong="G2532"\w* \w would|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w handed|strong="G3860"\w* \w him|strong="G4160"\w* \w over|strong="G3860"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w*.”\f + \fr 18:30 \ft Their answer seems a bit petulant. I gather that the deal they thought they had with Pilate included that he would just take Jesus and condemn Him. Pilate's attitude takes them by surprise.\f*
\v 31 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\nd \w You|strong="G5210"\w*\nd* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w judge|strong="G2919"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*.” \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w We|strong="G2249"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w permitted|strong="G1832"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* execute \w anyone|strong="G3762"\w*.”\f + \fr 18:31 \ft Pilate was rubbing salt in their wound, reminding them that they were a subjugated people—he knew they wanted to kill Jesus, so when he tells them to judge Him he forces them to acknowledge their subjugation. (Roman governors were probably not appointed on the basis of being nice.)\f*
\v 32 (\w This|strong="G3588"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w fulfill|strong="G4137"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w statement|strong="G3056"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w made|strong="G4137"\w*, indicating \w what|strong="G3739"\w* sort \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w death|strong="G2288"\w* \w He|strong="G3739"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G3195"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w die|strong="G2288"\w*.)\f + \fr 18:32 \ft Jesus had to die on a cross, but crucifixion was a Roman procedure, not Jewish—they would probably have stoned Him.\f*
\s1 Pilate and Jesus
\p 
\v 33 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w went|strong="G1525"\w* \w back|strong="G3825"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Praetorium|strong="G4232"\w*, \w called|strong="G3004"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*?”
\v 34 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w* \w him|strong="G1438"\w*, “\w Are|strong="G3778"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w on|strong="G4012"\w* \w your|strong="G1438"\w* \w own|strong="G1438"\w*, \w or|strong="G2228"\w* \w did|strong="G2228"\w* others inform \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*?”
\v 35 \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* answered \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w I|strong="G1473"\w*'m \w not|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jew|strong="G2453"\w*, \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w*? \w Your|strong="G4674"\w* \w own|strong="G4674"\w* \w nation|strong="G1484"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w chief|strong="G2532"\w* priests \w handed|strong="G3860"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w over|strong="G3860"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*. \w What|strong="G5101"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w done|strong="G4160"\w*?”
\v 36 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* answered: “\nd \w My|strong="G1699"\w*\nd* kingdom \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*. \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* kingdom \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w my|strong="G1699"\w* subjects \w would|strong="G1510"\w* fight \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w delivered|strong="G3860"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*; \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \nd \w now|strong="G1161"\w*\nd* \w my|strong="G1699"\w* kingdom \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w here|strong="G1782"\w*.”\f + \fr 18:36 \ft But one day, probably quite soon now, it will be.\f*
\v 37 \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w You|strong="G4771"\w* \nd \w are|strong="G1510"\w*\nd* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*?” \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w As|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w*; \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w born|strong="G1080"\w*. \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G3754"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w world|strong="G2889"\w*, \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w testify|strong="G3140"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Truth. \w Everyone|strong="G3956"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* Truth hears \w my|strong="G3956"\w* \w voice|strong="G5456"\w*.”
\v 38 \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w What|strong="G5101"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* truth?”\f + \fr 18:38 \ft Apparently the question was rhetorical; he didn't wait for an answer.\f*
\s2 Barabbas
\p \w Upon|strong="G1722"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w crime|strong="G2147"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G2532"\w*.\f + \fr 18:38 \ft Comparing John with Luke 23:4-12 it appears that between verses 38 and 39 here Jesus was sent to Herod. Notice that Pilate declares Jesus to be innocent.\f*
\v 39 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w we|strong="G1161"\w*\f + \fr 18:39 \ft I here follow the best line of transmission, although representing only some 20% of the manuscripts. Upon reflection this reading looks correct—how could the Jews have a custom that placed an obligation on their conquerors?\f* \w have|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* \w custom|strong="G4914"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w I|strong="G1161"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* release \w someone|strong="G1520"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Passover|strong="G3957"\w*; \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w do|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w want|strong="G1014"\w* me \w to|strong="G2443"\w* release \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w King|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G1520"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*?”
\v 40 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w they|strong="G1161"\w* \w all|strong="G3361"\w* \w cried|strong="G2905"\w* \w out|strong="G2905"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Not|strong="G3361"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* fellow, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* Barabbas!” Well, Barabbas \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G1510"\w* bandit!
\c 19
\s1 Soldiers mock Jesus
\m 
\v 1 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* flogged.
\v 2 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4757"\w* \w twisted|strong="G4120"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* [poisonous] thorns \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G2007"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1537"\w* \w His|strong="G2007"\w* \w head|strong="G2776"\w*; \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* threw \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w purple|strong="G4210"\w* \w robe|strong="G2440"\w* \w around|strong="G4016"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*
\v 3 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* started \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Hail|strong="G5463"\w*, O \w King|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*!” \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* slapped \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w repeatedly|strong="G4475"\w*.
\s1 “Behold the Man!”
\p 
\v 4 \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w then|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Look|strong="G3708"\w*, \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w am|strong="G2532"\w* bringing \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w know|strong="G1097"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w crime|strong="G2147"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G2532"\w*.”\f + \fr 19:4 \ft Pilate's reasoning is not obvious to me, unless the normal procedure would be to get on with the execution. But Pilate is not happy and is looking for a way out; he had received a message from his wife in the meantime (Matthew 27:19). Perhaps he hoped they would be satisfied when they saw how much He had already suffered.\f*
\v 5 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w came|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w wearing|strong="G5409"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w crown|strong="G4735"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* thorns \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w purple|strong="G4210"\w* \w robe|strong="G2440"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \it Pilate\it* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Look|strong="G2400"\w* \w at|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* man!”
\v 6 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w chief|strong="G2532"\w* priests \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* operatives \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* shouted, \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Crucify|strong="G4717"\w*! \w Crucify|strong="G4717"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*!” \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\bd \w You|strong="G5210"\w*\bd* \w take|strong="G2983"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucify|strong="G4717"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w find|strong="G2147"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w crime|strong="G2147"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*.”\f + \fr 19:6 \ft This is the second time that Pilate declares that he finds no crime in Jesus. He is declaring His innocence, so he will knowingly condemn an innocent man.\f*
\v 7 \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* answered \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w We|strong="G2249"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w a|strong="G2192"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w according|strong="G2596"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w our|strong="G2316"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w ought|strong="G3784"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* die, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w himself|strong="G1438"\w* ‘\w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*’!”
\s1 Pilate and Jesus, again
\p 
\v 8 Hey, \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* heard \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w statement|strong="G3056"\w* \w he|strong="G3778"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w more|strong="G3123"\w* \w afraid|strong="G5399"\w* \w than|strong="G3123"\w* ever!\f + \fr 19:8 \ft And not without reason. The conversation recorded in 18:33-37 would certainly have impressed Pilate and left him troubled. Then his wife added fuel to the fire. And now this. Pilate was not a religious type, presumably, but Jesus was impressive! Pilate was in over his head, and knew it.\f*
\v 9 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w back|strong="G3825"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Praetorium|strong="G4232"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G1525"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, “\bd \w Where|strong="G4159"\w*\bd* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w*?” \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* answer \w him|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 10 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w speaking|strong="G2980"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \bd \nd \w me|strong="G1473"\w*\nd*\bd*? Don'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucify|strong="G4717"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* release \w you|strong="G4771"\w*?”
\v 11 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* answered: “\w You|strong="G4771"\w* \w would|strong="G1510"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w authority|strong="G1849"\w* \w over|strong="G3860"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w at|strong="G2596"\w* \w all|strong="G2596"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w it|strong="G1487"\w* \w had|strong="G2192"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* \w given|strong="G1325"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w from|strong="G2596"\w* Above.\f + \fr 19:11 \ft Pilate represented the Roman empire, the greatest temporal power at that time (whose ruler was supposedly divine), but Jesus calmly affirms that there is a higher power and that He represents that higher power—and Pilate believed Him! Pilate wanted no part of killing Jesus, and really tried to avoid it, but the Jews did an end run.\f* \w Therefore|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w handed|strong="G3860"\w* \w me|strong="G1325"\w* \w over|strong="G3860"\w* \w to|strong="G2596"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w has|strong="G2192"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w greater|strong="G3173"\w* sin.”
\s1 The Jews best Pilate
\p 
\v 12 \w From|strong="G1537"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* moment \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* really \w tried|strong="G2212"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* release \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*; \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w kept|strong="G4160"\w* \w shouting|strong="G2905"\w*, \w saying|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w If|strong="G1437"\w* \w you|strong="G1437"\w* release \w this|strong="G3778"\w* fellow \w you|strong="G1437"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w friend|strong="G5384"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w Caesar|strong="G2541"\w*'s! \w Whoever|strong="G3956"\w* \w makes|strong="G4160"\w* \w himself|strong="G1438"\w* \w a|strong="G1437"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* opposing \w Caesar|strong="G2541"\w*!”\f + \fr 19:12 \ft Oops! Pilate owed his position to Caesar's good graces, and simply could not afford to do something that could be construed (even with a little twisting) as treason. He is beaten and knows it.\f*
\v 13 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w*, \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* hearing \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w statement|strong="G3056"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w led|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w outside|strong="G1854"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w sat|strong="G2523"\w* \w down|strong="G2523"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* judgment \w seat|strong="G2523"\w*, \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w* \w called|strong="G3004"\w* ‘Stone \w Pavement|strong="G3038"\w*’, \w while|strong="G1161"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w Hebrew|strong="G1447"\w* ‘\it Gabatha\it*’\f + \fr 19:13 \ft This action signaled that he had reached a decision and was about to give the verdict.\f*
\v 14 (\w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w day|strong="G3904"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w preparation|strong="G3904"\w* \w for|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Passover|strong="G3957"\w*;\f + \fr 19:14 \ft If the Jews were still preparing for the Passover, then Jesus and His disciples observed it a day early—which must have seemed strange to the disciples. But as the ultimate Passover Lamb, Jesus had to die on that preparation day.\f* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w about|strong="G5613"\w* six \w a|strong="G5613"\w*.m.),\f + \fr 19:14 \ft The Text says “the sixth hour”, which in Roman time is six a.m. If it were Jewish time it would be noon, which will not work here. Actually it says ‘around’ or ‘about’ six—I assume that it was a little after the hour.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*, “\w Look|strong="G3708"\w* \w at|strong="G1161"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w*!”
\v 15 \w But|strong="G1487"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* shouted, “\w Out|strong="G2905"\w*! \w Out|strong="G2905"\w*! \w Crucify|strong="G4717"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*!” \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Shall|strong="G3361"\w* \w I|strong="G1487"\w* \w crucify|strong="G4717"\w* \w your|strong="G2192"\w* \nd \w king|strong="G3588"\w*\nd*?” \w The|strong="G3588"\w* chief priests \w answered|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w We|strong="G1487"\w* \w have|strong="G2192"\w* \w no|strong="G3756"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w* \w but|strong="G1487"\w* \w Caesar|strong="G2541"\w*!”\f + \fr 19:15 \ft Ah, Pilate gets his ‘pound of flesh’. He doubtless knew a bit about Jewish culture and religion, including their messianic hopes. In effect the Jews here deny the Messiah—Caesar is their only king! Pilate rescued this bit of satisfaction out of a bad deal.\f*
\v 16 \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w he|strong="G3588"\w* \w handed|strong="G3860"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w over|strong="G3860"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2443"\w* \w be|strong="G3588"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w*.
\s1 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w*
\p \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w took|strong="G3880"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w and|strong="G2424"\w* lead \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* away.
\v 17 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* carrying \w His|strong="G1438"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w* \w called|strong="G3004"\w* ‘\w Skull|strong="G2898"\w*’, \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w Hebrew|strong="G1447"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w called|strong="G3004"\w* ‘\it Golgotha\it*’;
\v 18 \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* \w others|strong="G3588"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w on|strong="G1161"\w* \w either|strong="G1782"\w* \w side|strong="G1782"\w*, \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w middle|strong="G3319"\w*.
\v 19 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* notice, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G5087"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w inscription|strong="G5102"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w*:
\pc \w JESUS|strong="G2424"\w* \w THE|strong="G2532"\w* NATSOREAN\f + \fr 19:19 \ft That Pilate put “\nd the\nd* Natsorean” (\nd not\nd* Natsarene [Nazarene]) indicates that he had researched Jesus. The reference is to Isaiah 11:1; Jesus was David's Branch, the Messiah. Pilate was making a statement.\f*
\pc \w THE|strong="G2532"\w* \w KING|strong="G3588"\w* \w OF|strong="G2532"\w* \w THE|strong="G2532"\w* \w JEWS|strong="G2453"\w*.
\m 
\v 20 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w read|strong="G1125"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* notice, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w near|strong="G1451"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w city|strong="G4172"\w*; \w further|strong="G4183"\w*, \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w Hebrew|strong="G1447"\w*, \w Greek|strong="G1676"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Latin|strong="G4515"\w*!\f + \fr 19:20 \ft Comparing the other Gospels, the full inscription was, ‘This is Jesus the Natsorean, the King of the Jews’. To put all of that in three languages would require a board of fair size. But why did Pilate use \nd three\nd* languages? One would have been enough (it was customary to put the crime over the victim's head). I take it that Pilate was \bd not\bd* happy, having been bested by the Jews; and as I have said above, I think he was personally convinced that Jesus was a king. By putting ‘this is the king of the Jews’ he was making a statement, one that virtually any literate person would be able to read, given the three languages.\f*
\v 21 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* chief priests \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w*, “Don'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w write|strong="G1125"\w*, ‘\w The|strong="G3588"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*’, \w but|strong="G3361"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* fellow \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, ‘\w I|strong="G3754"\w* \w am|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w king|strong="G3588"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*.’ ”
\v 22 \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* answered, “\w What|strong="G3739"\w* \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G3588"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w*, \w I|strong="G3739"\w* \w have|strong="G3588"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w*!”\f + \fr 19:22 \ft The chief priests have gotten all they are going to get out of Pilate; he was making a statement, but he was also getting back at them a little bit.\f*
\s2 Psalm 22:18 is fulfilled
\p 
\v 23 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4757"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w clothes|strong="G2440"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w made|strong="G4160"\w* \w four|strong="G5064"\w* \w parts|strong="G3313"\w*, \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w part|strong="G3313"\w* \w for|strong="G1223"\w* \w each|strong="G1538"\w* \w soldier|strong="G4757"\w*.\f + \fr 19:23 \ft This probably means that Jesus was left without any; one final bit of humiliation.\f* \w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w His|strong="G1223"\w* \w tunic|strong="G5509"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tunic|strong="G5509"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* seamless, \w woven|strong="G5307"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1538"\w* \w piece|strong="G3313"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* top.
\v 24 \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w among|strong="G4314"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1438"\w*, “\w Let|strong="G1510"\w*'s \w not|strong="G3361"\w* rip \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* toss \w for|strong="G4012"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w*, \it to see\it* \w whose|strong="G5101"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w*,” \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w fulfilled|strong="G4137"\w* \w which|strong="G3588"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w*:
\q1 “\w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w divided|strong="G1266"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w clothes|strong="G2440"\w* \w among|strong="G4314"\w* \w themselves|strong="G1438"\w*,
\q2 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w for|strong="G4012"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w clothing|strong="G2440"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w cast|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w lot|strong="G2819"\w*.”
\m \w That|strong="G2443"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w why|strong="G5101"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4757"\w* \w did|strong="G4160"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w*.\f + \fr 19:24 \ft See Psalm 22:18. John seems to be affirming a cause/effect relationship. The centurion could have claimed the tunic, or whatever, but casting a lot had been prophesied.\f*
\s1 Jesus provides for His mother
\p 
\v 25 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*' \w mother|strong="G3384"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3137"\w* sister, \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Clopas|strong="G2832"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w Magdalene|strong="G3094"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w by|strong="G3844"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w*.
\v 26 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w seeing|strong="G3708"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* loved \w standing|strong="G3936"\w* \w by|strong="G3936"\w*, \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w*, “\w Woman|strong="G1135"\w*, \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w son|strong="G5207"\w*!”
\v 27 \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w*, “\w There|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w mother|strong="G3384"\w*!” \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w from|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w hour|strong="G5610"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w her|strong="G1438"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w his|strong="G1438"\w* \w home|strong="G1519"\w*.\f + \fr 19:27 \ft Notice that Jesus is still perfectly lucid. As Mary's oldest son, He was responsible for her well-being (we understand that Joseph was gone by now), so He passes that responsibility over to the Apostle John (the author of this Gospel); and John accepts it.\f*
\s1 The shout of victory
\p 
\v 28 \w After|strong="G3326"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w*, \w knowing|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w everything|strong="G3956"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w now|strong="G2235"\w* \w accomplished|strong="G5055"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G3956"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w might|strong="G3778"\w* \w be|strong="G3956"\w* \w fulfilled|strong="G5055"\w*, \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w I|strong="G3754"\w*'m \w thirsty|strong="G1372"\w*!”
\v 29 \w Now|strong="G3767"\w* \w a|strong="G4060"\w* \w vessel|strong="G4632"\w* \w full|strong="G3324"\w* \w of|strong="G4750"\w* \w sour|strong="G3690"\w* \w wine|strong="G3690"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* sitting \w there|strong="G3767"\w*; \w so|strong="G3767"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* filled \w a|strong="G4060"\w* \w sponge|strong="G4699"\w* \w with|strong="G3588"\w* \w sour|strong="G3690"\w* \w wine|strong="G3690"\w*, placed \w it|strong="G3588"\w* \w on|strong="G3588"\w* \w a|strong="G4060"\w* \w hyssop|strong="G5301"\w*, \w and|strong="G3767"\w* \w put|strong="G4060"\w* \w it|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G3767"\w* \w His|strong="G3588"\w* \w mouth|strong="G4750"\w*.
\v 30 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w received|strong="G2983"\w*\f + \fr 19:30 \ft From the word ‘received’ it appears that He did swallow some. Since sour wine was not used at the Passover, this does not conflict with the Lord's statement in the upper room (Matthew 26:29) that He would not drink of “this product of the vine”. All four Evangelists mention the sour wine. There was evidently a pot/vessel full of it (the soldiers were in for many hours of vigil and that was what they drank). The mocking offer mentioned in Luke 23:36 happened before the darkness; the other three accounts after. The offer recorded in Matthew 27:48 and Mark 15:36 was triggered by Jesus' cry, “My God, my God…” The one in John 19:29-30 by His saying, “I am thirsty”. I venture to suggest that there was an interval between His despairing cry and His statement—after the cry He may have lapsed back into silence for a bit; He was trying to make contact with the Father. It may be that the sour wine sort of ‘wet His whistle’ so He could let out His shout of victory.\f* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w sour|strong="G3690"\w* \w wine|strong="G3690"\w*, \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “Paid \w in|strong="G2532"\w* full!!”\f + \fr 19:30 \ft Matthew, Mark and Luke all affirm that Jesus gave a great shout, but without giving the content. I take it that John supplies that information, although he does not mention that it was a shout. “Τετελεσται”—that was what they wrote on bills and promissory notes when they were paid off = ‘paid in full’. When something is shouted the individual sounds can be distorted, but John was right there and could read His lips, if necessary. It was a shout of victory: “We did it!” “Finished!” “Paid in full!”\f* \w And|strong="G2532"\w* bowing \w His|strong="G2983"\w* \w head|strong="G2776"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* dismissed \w His|strong="G2983"\w* \w spirit|strong="G4151"\w*.\f + \fr 19:30 \ft That is right—the cross did not kill Jesus, He just told His spirit to leave. In John 10:17-18 he was very clear: no one could take His life from Him, but He could lay it down (please see the note at John 10:18).\f*
\s1 A soldier spears His side
\p 
\v 31 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w Preparation|strong="G3904"\w* \w Day|strong="G2250"\w*, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w bodies|strong="G4983"\w* \w should|strong="G3306"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w remain|strong="G3306"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w cross|strong="G4716"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Sabbath|strong="G4521"\w* (\w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w Sabbath|strong="G4521"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w high|strong="G3173"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w*), \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w* \w requested|strong="G2065"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w their|strong="G2532"\w* \w legs|strong="G4628"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w broken|strong="G2608"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* removed.
\v 32 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4757"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w broke|strong="G2608"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w legs|strong="G4628"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w man|strong="G4413"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G3588"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G2532"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4957"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.
\v 33 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w upon|strong="G1909"\w* \w coming|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G1909"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w they|strong="G1161"\w* \w did|strong="G2064"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w break|strong="G2608"\w* \w His|strong="G1909"\w* \w legs|strong="G4628"\w*, \w since|strong="G5613"\w* \w they|strong="G1161"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w He|strong="G1161"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w already|strong="G2235"\w* \w died|strong="G2348"\w*.
\v 34 \w But|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w soldiers|strong="G4757"\w* \w pierced|strong="G3572"\w* \w His|strong="G2532"\w* \w side|strong="G4125"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w spear|strong="G3057"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w immediately|strong="G2112"\w* blood \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w water|strong="G5204"\w* \w came|strong="G1831"\w* \w out|strong="G1831"\w*.
\v 35 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w saw|strong="G1492"\w* \w has|strong="G3708"\w* \w testified|strong="G3140"\w*,\f + \fr 19:35 \ft John, the author of this Gospel, was right there (verses 25-26 above), so he could see very clearly what came out of Jesus' side—that the blood had separated was a clear sign of physical death. (I guess we don't need to know, really, just how the separation came about, whether by purely natural processes or with supernatural intervention; in any case, John is emphatic about what he saw.)\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w his|strong="G2532"\w* \w testimony|strong="G3141"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w true|strong="G3588"\w* (yes, \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w knows|strong="G1492"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w telling|strong="G3004"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* truth), \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w may|strong="G2532"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w*.
\v 36 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w happened|strong="G1096"\w* \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w should|strong="G3588"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w fulfilled|strong="G4137"\w*: “\w Not|strong="G3756"\w* \w a|strong="G1096"\w* \w bone|strong="G3747"\w* \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w His|strong="G3588"\w* \w will|strong="G3778"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* \w broken|strong="G4937"\w*.”\f + \fr 19:36 \ft See Exodus 12:46, Numbers 9:12 and Psalm 34:20.\f*
\v 37 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w* \w another|strong="G2087"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \w look|strong="G3708"\w* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w Him|strong="G3739"\w* \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w pierced|strong="G1574"\w*.”\f + \fr 19:37 \ft See Zechariah 12:10.\f*
\s1 Jesus is buried
\p 
\v 38 \w After|strong="G3326"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w Joseph|strong="G2501"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w from|strong="G2064"\w* Arimathea (\w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w secretly|strong="G2928"\w* \w for|strong="G1223"\w* \w fear|strong="G5401"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*), \w requested|strong="G2065"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w might|strong="G2532"\w* remove \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Pilate|strong="G4091"\w* \w gave|strong="G2010"\w* \w permission|strong="G2010"\w*. \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* removed \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*' \w body|strong="G4983"\w*.
\v 39 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w Nicodemus|strong="G3530"\w* \w also|strong="G2532"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w*\f + \fr 19:39 \ft He helped Joseph take down the body, and they transported it to the tomb in a linen sheet (Matthew 27:59).\f* (\w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w at|strong="G4314"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2532"\w* \w by|strong="G4314"\w* \w night|strong="G3571"\w*), \w bringing|strong="G5342"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w mixture|strong="G3395"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w myrrh|strong="G4666"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* aloes, \w about|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w hundred|strong="G1540"\w* \w pounds|strong="G3046"\w*.\f + \fr 19:39 \ft Do you suppose they just ‘happened’ to have a hundred pounds of expensive spices lying around? Almost certainly everything had been prepared before hand, including the tomb, on purpose. These men had doubtless received specific instructions and were waiting in the wings to perform their part.\f*
\v 40 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w took|strong="G2983"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*' \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w wrapped|strong="G1210"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w linen|strong="G3608"\w* strips, \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* aromatic spices, \w according|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w burial|strong="G1779"\w* \w custom|strong="G1485"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*.
\v 41 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w crucified|strong="G4717"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w garden|strong="G2779"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w garden|strong="G2779"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w new|strong="G2537"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w no|strong="G3762"\w* \w one|strong="G3762"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* buried.\f + \fr 19:41 \ft Isaiah 53:9 affirms that the Messiah would have a rich man's burial, and He did—a brand new tomb (rather large), and a hundred pounds of expensive spices. The body of an executed criminal would normally be treated ignominiously, and I imagine that was what the high priests intended, but the Father made sure that the Son received an honorable burial. Matthew 27:60 informs us that Joseph had himself prepared that tomb, and he did so at a spot near Golgotha. The next verse (here in John) indicates that this was done on purpose, for the reason mentioned. Joseph and Nicodemus clearly did what they did under divine guidance, and of course God knew that the tomb would need to be near Golgotha, etc.\f*
\v 42 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w where|strong="G5087"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w put|strong="G5087"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*, \w because|strong="G3754"\w* \w of|strong="G1223"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*' \w Preparation|strong="G3904"\w* \w Day|strong="G3904"\w*, \w since|strong="G3754"\w* \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w nearby|strong="G1451"\w*.
\c 20
\ms1 Resurrection Day\f + \fr 20:0 \ft For a harmonization of all the details furnished by the four Gospel accounts, please see the Appendix: “Harmonizing the accounts of the Resurrection”.\f*
\s1 The empty tomb
\m 
\v 1 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w first|strong="G1520"\w* \w day|strong="G4521"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w week|strong="G4521"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w Magdalene|strong="G3094"\w* \w comes|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w* \w early|strong="G4404"\w*, \w while|strong="G1161"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* \w still|strong="G2089"\w* \w dark|strong="G4653"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* sees \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w stone|strong="G3037"\w* \w has|strong="G1510"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* removed \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w*.
\v 2 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w runs|strong="G5143"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w comes|strong="G2064"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w Simon|strong="G4613"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G3739"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w*, \w whom|strong="G3739"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w loved|strong="G5368"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w They|strong="G2532"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* taken \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w out|strong="G1537"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w*\f + \fr 20:2 \ft “We”—presumably Magdalene is referring to the other women who were with her, as in the parallel accounts.\f* don'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w where|strong="G4226"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G5087"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*!”\f + \fr 20:2 \ft Pure supposition—she had not looked in the tomb; she jumped to a false conclusion. It is clear that there was no longer a shining angel sitting on the stone outside (Matthew 28:2).\f*
\v 3 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G3588"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* \w took|strong="G2532"\w* \w off|strong="G1831"\w*, heading \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w*.
\v 4 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* started \w running|strong="G5143"\w* \w together|strong="G3674"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* outran \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* got \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w*.
\v 5 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w stooping|strong="G3879"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w look|strong="G3879"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* sees \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w linen|strong="G3608"\w* strips \w lying|strong="G2749"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w*; \w however|strong="G3305"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w go|strong="G1525"\w* \w in|strong="G1525"\w*.
\v 6 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* following \w him|strong="G3588"\w* \w comes|strong="G2064"\w* \w Simon|strong="G4613"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2064"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w sees|strong="G2334"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w linen|strong="G3608"\w* strips \w lying|strong="G2749"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w*,
\v 7 \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* facecloth\f + \fr 20:7 \ft That there was a facecloth indicates that there was not a sheet that covered the body from head to toe (as in the ‘shroud of Turin’). This was also true of Lazarus (John 11:44).\f* \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w been|strong="G1510"\w* \w on|strong="G1909"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w head|strong="G2776"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w lying|strong="G2749"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w linen|strong="G3608"\w* strips, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* folded \w up|strong="G1519"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w separate|strong="G5565"\w* \w place|strong="G5117"\w*.
\s2 John sees and believes
\p 
\v 8 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w other|strong="G3588"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w* \w went|strong="G2064"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w too|strong="G2532"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* got \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w* \w first|strong="G4413"\w*; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w believed|strong="G4100"\w*.\f + \fr 20:8 \ft What did John ‘see’ that made him ‘believe’? He saw the linen strips ‘lying’, that is, in the form of the body, only there was no body inside them! If someone had stolen the body, as Magdalene supposed, they would have taken the wrapped package (much easier to carry, not to mention 100 pounds of expensive spices) and there would have been no linen strips. If someone had unwrapped the body there would have been a mound of linen strips and spices piled up (how much cloth would it take to wrap up a hundred pounds of spices?). No, Jesus simply passed through the cloth, as He would later pass through the wall, leaving the package like a mummy or empty cocoon. When John saw that he understood that the only possible explanation was resurrection.\f*
\v 9 (\w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w did|strong="G1492"\w* \w not|strong="G3764"\w* \w yet|strong="G3764"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w Scripture|strong="G1124"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G3754"\w* \w had|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G1163"\w* \w rise|strong="G1163"\w* \w from|strong="G1537"\w* \w among|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w dead|strong="G3498"\w*.)\f + \fr 20:9 \ft But they should have; Jesus had told them repeatedly. But wait just a minute! Where in the OT is there such a Scripture? John wrote this Gospel over fifteen years after the other three had been ‘published’ and were in circulation, so his term ‘Scripture’ may be referring to them.\f*
\v 10 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G4314"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w went|strong="G3101"\w* \w back|strong="G3825"\w* \w home|strong="G1438"\w*.
\s1 Jesus appears first to Magdalene
\p 
\v 11 \w Well|strong="G5613"\w* \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w outside|strong="G1854"\w* \w at|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w*, \w crying|strong="G2799"\w*.\f + \fr 20:11 \ft When the disciples took off running, of course Magdalene followed them back to the tomb. But she was winded, and could not keep up with them (actually, in that culture women probably seldom ran, so she would really be out of breath, but she was not about to be left out of the action, either). The Jerusalem at that time probably covered a relatively small area; it was probably no more than half a mile from the house to the tomb, if that, so she may have arrived as they were leaving; if not, they would pass her on the road.\f* \w Then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w while|strong="G5613"\w* \w she|strong="G1161"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w crying|strong="G2799"\w*, \w she|strong="G1161"\w* \w stooped|strong="G3879"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w look|strong="G3879"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1519"\w* \w tomb|strong="G3419"\w*.
\v 12 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w sees|strong="G2334"\w* \w two|strong="G1417"\w* angels\f + \fr 20:12 \ft How did John know they were angels? He had just been there and knew there were no human beings around (the guards were presumably gone before the two got there). The angels were in white, but probably not shining, or Magdalene would have been shaken out of her despair. She was so locked in to her sorrow that not even seeing the wrappings collapsed without the body sank in.\f* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w white|strong="G3022"\w*, \w sitting|strong="G2516"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w head|strong="G2776"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w at|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w feet|strong="G4228"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w body|strong="G4983"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w had|strong="G2424"\w* \w lain|strong="G2749"\w*.
\v 13 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3754"\w*, “\w Woman|strong="G1135"\w*, \w why|strong="G5101"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w crying|strong="G2799"\w*?” \w She|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w removed|strong="G5087"\w* \w my|strong="G5087"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* don'\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w where|strong="G4226"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G5087"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.”
\v 14 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G1519"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w turned|strong="G4762"\w* \w around|strong="G3694"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G1492"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w standing|strong="G2476"\w* \w there|strong="G2532"\w*, \w yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w know|strong="G1492"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w*.
\v 15 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w her|strong="G3754"\w*: “\w Woman|strong="G1135"\w*, \w why|strong="G5101"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w crying|strong="G2799"\w*? \w Whom|strong="G5101"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w seeking|strong="G2212"\w*?” \w She|strong="G3754"\w*, \w supposing|strong="G1380"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w He|strong="G3754"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w gardener|strong="G2780"\w*, \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Sir|strong="G2962"\w*, \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* carried \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w away|strong="G5087"\w*, \w tell|strong="G3004"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w* \w where|strong="G4226"\w* \w you|strong="G4771"\w* \w put|strong="G5087"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w and|strong="G2962"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G5101"\w* remove \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*.”
\v 16 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w her|strong="G3137"\w*, “\w Mary|strong="G3137"\w*!” \w Turning|strong="G4762"\w* \w she|strong="G3739"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w Him|strong="G3739"\w*, “Raboni!” (\w which|strong="G3739"\w* \w means|strong="G3004"\w* ‘\w Teacher|strong="G1320"\w*’).
\v 17 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w her|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Stop|strong="G3361"\w* clinging \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*,\f + \fr 20:17 \ft That is what the Text says. I take it that Magdalene was an emotive person, capable of sudden ‘ups’ and ‘downs’. From the way the Lord pronounced her name she knew who it was; from deep sorrow she swings to a transport of joy and impulsively throws her arms around Him. Hey, she is \bd not\bd* thinking of how this is going to read 2,000 years later; in fact, she is not thinking at all, just feeling.\f* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w yet|strong="G2532"\w* \w ascended|strong="G3588"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*;\f + \fr 20:17 \ft The causal connection here seems difficult to us—what did His not having ascended have to do with it? Various suggestions have been offered. My guess is as follows: Magdalene had not heard the teaching in the Upper Room, more precisely, John16:7. “I am telling you the truth: it is to your advantage that I go away, because if I do not go away the Enabler will not come to you, but if I go I will send Him to you.” She had just gotten her Master back and was not about to turn Him loose—she was feeling, not thinking. But Jesus had to ascend so He could send the Enabler, which would be better for everybody. She wants to hang on to Him, but He tells her to stop; the old relationships are gone, everything is now new. (Within a very few minutes He will allow the other women to hold His feet, so mere physical contact is not the problem; in fact, He will later invite the disciples to touch Him.)\f* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w go|strong="G4198"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* brothers\f + \fr 20:17 \ft He does not just reprimand her, He gives her something to do. But just who are the “brothers”? Since the angel had told the other women to tell the disciples, I am inclined to imagine that the Lord sends her to His half brothers, although she started out with the disciples (next verse).\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w say|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, ‘\w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w am|strong="G1473"\w* ascending \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w*—\w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*.’ ”
\v 18 \w Mary|strong="G3137"\w* \w Magdalene|strong="G3094"\w* goes \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w*, reporting \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w she|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w seen|strong="G3708"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w had|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w these|strong="G3778"\w* \w things|strong="G3778"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w her|strong="G3708"\w*.
\s1 Disciples commissioned
\p 
\v 19 \w Then|strong="G3767"\w* \w at|strong="G1519"\w* \w evening|strong="G3798"\w* \w on|strong="G1519"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w first|strong="G1520"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w week|strong="G4521"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w doors|strong="G2374"\w* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w locked|strong="G2808"\w* \w where|strong="G3699"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* assembled, \w for|strong="G1519"\w* \w fear|strong="G5401"\w* \w of|strong="G2250"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Jews|strong="G2453"\w*, \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w middle|strong="G3319"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w Peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*!”
\v 20 \w And|strong="G2532"\w* \w upon|strong="G5495"\w* \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w showed|strong="G1166"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w His|strong="G3708"\w* \w hands|strong="G5495"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G3708"\w* \w side|strong="G4125"\w*. \w Well|strong="G2532"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* overjoyed \w when|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w saw|strong="G3708"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*!
\v 21 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*: “\w Peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w to|strong="G3004"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*!\f + \fr 20:21 \ft This is what He said “again”, having already said it (verse 19).\f* \w Just|strong="G2531"\w* \w as|strong="G2531"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Father|strong="G3962"\w* \w sent|strong="G3992"\w* \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w also|strong="G2504"\w* \w send|strong="G3992"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*.”\f + \fr 20:21 \ft This is tremendous! In my own experience (as a missionary, son of missionaries), I have seldom heard a missionary challenge based on John 20:21. The champion is Matthew 28:19-20, ‘the great commission’, followed by Mark 16:15 and perhaps Acts 1:8; but John 20:21? “Just as… so also”—Jesus is sending us just like the Father sent Him. So how did They do it? The Father determined and the Son obeyed: “Behold, I have come to do your will, O God” (Hebrews 10:7). And what was that will? To destroy Satan (Hebrews 2:14) and undo his works (1 John 3:8). Since Jesus did indeed defeat Satan (Colossians 2:15, Ephesians 1:20-21, etc.) what is left for us is the undoing of his works. For more on this subject see my article, “Biblical Spiritual Warfare”, available from my site, www.prunch.org.\f*
\v 22 Upon \w saying|strong="G3004"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w breathed|strong="G1720"\w* \w on|strong="G4151"\w* \w them|strong="G3004"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*: “\w Receive|strong="G2983"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*!\f + \fr 20:22 \ft There is no definite article with “Holy Spirit” and I hesitate to add it. Perhaps we should try thinking of ‘Holy Spirit’ as a proper name.\f*
\v 23 \w To|strong="G5100"\w* whomever \w you|strong="G5100"\w* forgive \w the|strong="G3588"\w* sins,\f + \fr 20:23 \ft This is a literal rendering, but I hesitate to change it. The primary reference is presumably to the sins of that person, but it is sometimes necessary to pronounce forgiveness for sins of past generations (see 2 Samuel 21:1-14).\f* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* forgiven \w to|strong="G5100"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*; \w to|strong="G5100"\w* whomever \w you|strong="G5100"\w* \w retain|strong="G2902"\w*, \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w have|strong="G5100"\w* \w been|strong="G5100"\w* \w retained|strong="G2902"\w*.”\f + \fr 20:23 \ft That is what the Text says, “have been”. The idea seems to be that sins are already retained (as soon as a sin is committed it is on the account); Jesus gives them the prerogative to change that situation, undoing the retaining, as it were. Presumably the forgiving and retaining have to do with the consequences of the sin in this life (not for salvation). I take it that the undoing of Satan's works (1 John 3:8) must reverse consequences (to the extent that this may be possible). Since Satan is involved in all sin, indirectly at least (or so I imagine), I conclude that verse 23 here falls within the competence of anyone who has the Holy Spirit.\f*
\s1 Thomas
\p 
\v 24 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w one|strong="G1520"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w the|strong="G1537"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w*, \w Thomas|strong="G2381"\w* (\w called|strong="G3004"\w* Twin), \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w*.
\v 25 \w So|strong="G3767"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w other|strong="G1161"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w We|strong="G1437"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w seen|strong="G3708"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w*!” \w But|strong="G1161"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w If|strong="G1437"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w do|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w see|strong="G3708"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* nail prints \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w hands|strong="G5495"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w finger|strong="G1147"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* nail prints, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w side|strong="G4125"\w*, \w I|strong="G1473"\w* \w will|strong="G2532"\w* \bd \nd \w not|strong="G3756"\w*\nd*\bd* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w*!”\f + \fr 20:25 \ft Thomas is very emphatic. Jesus is dead and his hopes are too! (Presumably he had watched the crucifixion from a distance.)\f*
\p 
\v 26 \w Well|strong="G2532"\w* \w after|strong="G3326"\w* \w eight|strong="G3638"\w* \w days|strong="G2250"\w*\f + \fr 20:26 \ft Their method of calculation included the day from which the count was made (as they do in Brazil as well), so this is the next Sunday.\f* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w inside|strong="G2080"\w* \w again|strong="G3825"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Thomas|strong="G2381"\w* \w with|strong="G3326"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*. \w The|strong="G2532"\w* \w doors|strong="G2374"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w locked|strong="G2808"\w* [\w again|strong="G3825"\w*]; \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w came|strong="G2064"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w stood|strong="G2476"\w* \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w middle|strong="G3319"\w*, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w Peace|strong="G1515"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*!”
\v 27 \w Then|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w Thomas|strong="G2381"\w*: “\w Bring|strong="G5342"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w finger|strong="G1147"\w* \w here|strong="G5602"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w perceive|strong="G3708"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w hands|strong="G5495"\w*; \w bring|strong="G5342"\w* \w your|strong="G2532"\w* \w hand|strong="G5495"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w put|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w into|strong="G1519"\w* \w my|strong="G3708"\w* \w side|strong="G4125"\w*;\f + \fr 20:27 \ft Since Jesus had not been there to hear Thomas, how did He know what he had said? We know the answer, but it delivered a knockout punch to Thomas. Evidently he did not try to touch Jesus, but without further ado said, “My Lord and my God!”\f* \w do|strong="G1096"\w* \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w be|strong="G1096"\w* unbelieving \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w believing|strong="G4103"\w*!”
\v 28 \w Thomas|strong="G2381"\w* \w answered|strong="G3004"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, “\w My|strong="G1473"\w* \w Lord|strong="G2962"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w my|strong="G1473"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*!”
\v 29 \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w says|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*: “\w Because|strong="G3754"\w* \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* observed \w me|strong="G1473"\w*, \w you|strong="G3754"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* \w believed|strong="G4100"\w*. \w Blessed|strong="G3107"\w* \w are|strong="G3588"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w believe|strong="G4100"\w* \w without|strong="G3361"\w* \w seeing|strong="G3708"\w*!”\f + \fr 20:29 \ft This blessing includes \nd us\nd*.\f*
\s1 Why this book
\p 
\v 30 \w Now|strong="G2532"\w* \w then|strong="G3767"\w*, \w Jesus|strong="G2424"\w* \w actually|strong="G2532"\w* \w performed|strong="G4160"\w* \w many|strong="G4183"\w* \w other|strong="G4183"\w* miraculous \w signs|strong="G4592"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w presence|strong="G1799"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w His|strong="G1722"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w*, \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w written|strong="G1125"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w this|strong="G3778"\w* \w book|strong="G3588"\w*;
