\v 11 \w Simon|strong="G4613"\w* \w Peter|strong="G4074"\w* got \w up|strong="G1519"\w*\f + \fr 21:11 \ft That is what the Text says. Well, what do you suppose he did when he got to land, since he obviously got there well before the others. From verse 12 I gather that Peter had not ventured to speak. He is wet and therefore cold, and there is a fire. I bet he went straight to the fire and squatted down to warm himself, but he was too embarrassed to attempt a conversation. So he welcomes a chance to do something and jumps up when Jesus asks for fish.\f* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w dragged|strong="G1670"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w net|strong="G1350"\w* \w onto|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w land|strong="G1093"\w*, \w full|strong="G3324"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w one|strong="G3588"\w* \w hundred|strong="G1540"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w fifty-three|strong="G4004"\w* \w large|strong="G3173"\w* \w fish|strong="G2486"\w* [!]; \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \it although\it* \w being|strong="G1510"\w* \w so|strong="G3767"\w* \w many|strong="G5118"\w*, \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w net|strong="G1350"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w torn|strong="G4977"\w*.\f + \fr 21:11 \ft Like, wow! They were evidently special fish, all large. But why 153? I do not know. The whole thing is supernatural, including the net not tearing.\f*
